-- T1 value restriction: an expansive (application) binding must NOT be
-- generalized, so its type stays monomorphic.  `c = poly poly` is an application
-- whose result type `a -> a` is polymorphic; without the value restriction `c`
-- would generalize and both `c 1` and `c "two"` would typecheck — the classic
-- polymorphic-mutable-reference / let-should-not-generalize soundness hole.  With
-- the value restriction `c` is monomorphic, so using it at Int and String inside
-- one tuple is a type error (same on the oracle and the self-hosted typechecker).
poly x = x
c = poly poly
pair = (c 1, c "two")
